config BR2_PACKAGE_GT_BE98_BR_OPENSSH
	bool "gt-be98-br-openssh"
	select BR2_PACKAGE_ZLIB
	help
	  OpenSSH 10.2p1 built from the hash-verified upstream tarball
	  for the /usr/br island, providing sftp-server (+ the scp/sftp/
	  ssh/ssh-keygen tools). openssl 3.6.2 (our gt-be98-br-openssl
	  /usr/br build) is linked STATICALLY (the device ships only
	  openssl 1.1 - a dynamic link would be an ABI mismatch); glibc
	  and zlib are dynamic against the device's own libs. Harvested
	  into the ASUS rootfs at /usr/br/libexec/sftp-server and
	  /usr/br/bin/{scp,sftp,ssh,ssh-keygen} by
	  board/gt-be98/rootfs-transform.sh. The S28 br-dropbear server
	  advertises the sftp subsystem pointing at this sftp-server, so
	  modern scp/sftp work against port 2223.
